After intensive consultations at the community level, the Save the Boral Movement put forward the following proposals:
a.	demarcation of the Boral river in accordance with CS plan and free the river area from encroachments; 
b.	capital dredging of the Boral river alongwith Padma and Jamuna to increase navigability;
c.	removal of the closed sluice gate at Charghat (officially known as the Charghat Regulator) as the same has reduced flow to the River from Padma, created islands on the Padma river and shrinked the river width;
d.	removal of the Atgharia sluicegate (officially known as the Atgharia Regulator) which has constructed one gate on Boral that now remain closed and has resulted in siltation of the River from AtghariauptoBonpara and encroachment over the same; alternatively, if the canal that flows from Kamardoho to Kachuati is widened and the Golakata bridge is slightly expanded, the river Boral can still flow through Charghat and fall into HuraSagor;
e.	removal of some small bridges and culverts from the River including the Bonpara Bypass Shorok Bridge, Bonpara Bazar Bridge, Koilar Khalia Bridge, Tiroil Bridge, Agran Bridge as they are affecting the navigability of the River;
f.	removal of Nunnagar embankment, Dohopara sluicegate, Chatmohor Notonbazar cross dam that have obstructed the flow of the river and construct full width bridge instead which will ensure flow over 50 kilometers of the River without requiring any excavation;
g.	re-connection of Boral and Gumani river by removing the earthern dam and sluice gate constructed respectively at Mathurapurand Dohopara in ChatmohorUpazilla;
h.	cancel lease agreements over the Boral river and refrain from entering into any future leasing arrangements.

